# NOTE: project-level .codeagent/ (config.json, hooks.json, skills/) is
# meant to be committed and shared with the team — this used to blanket-
# ignore the whole directory, which silently broke Hooks' "git-shareable"
# design (docs/17) and would have done the same to Skills (docs/18,
# PLAN.md Phase 4) before anyone noticed. Real local/session state lives in
# ~/.codeagent/sessions (the user's home directory), which was never
# actually inside a project's repo to begin with — the `~/.codeagent/`
# line below was a dead pattern anyway, since git doesn't expand `~`.
# Nothing needs excluding here; removed rather than left wrong.

# Local development planning (NOT for GitHub)
PLAN.md
*.local.md
NOTES.md

